ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It is a relatively comprehensive overview of the major geology of South Africa. I recommend it if you are going on the field trip, since it will help you appreciate the rocks you will see, but not otherwise, since it doesn't go into much depth about each topic.
You cover the complete geological history of South Africa. I wouldn't really recommend it unless you wanted to go on the field trip.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course increased my understanding of the non-paleontological aspects of geology, in particular as relates to South Africa. It will not be relevant to my dissertation research.
I learned that I actually don't know much about all of the different subfields of geology.
